In [[telecommunication]], the term '''local battery''' has the following meanings: 

<b>1.</b>  In [[telegraphy]], the source of [[power]] that actuates the telegraphic station recording instruments, as distinguished from the source of power that furnishes current to the [[line]].  

<b>2.</b>  In [[telephony]], a [[system]] in which each [[telephone]] instrument has its own source of power, as opposed to being powered from the [[central office]].  

<b>3.</b>  A source of local power for a telephone instrument.

Source: from [[Federal Standard 1037C]] and from [[MIL-STD-188]]